Midnight green
 
    Color coordinates

Midnight green (sometimes called Eagles green[citation needed]) is a dark shade of teal. This can be readily ascertained by noting the fact that this color's red value is zero, and also that its green and blue values are almost equal.

In culture[edit]

Sports

  • The Philadelphia Eagles use midnight green as their primary color.[1][2] In 1996, midnight green replaced Kelly green as the primary color used by the Eagles.[3]
